---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Palchat tech stack">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 pb-12 pt-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:pb-16 lg:pt-16">
    <header class="mb-8 space-y-3">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-400">About · Tech stack</p>
      <h1 class="text-balance text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        The stack behind Palchat.
      </h1>
      <p class="max-w-2xl text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
        A simple, modern setup focused on fast pages, small interactive tools, and boring-but-reliable infra.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-10 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-400">High-level view</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4 text-sm text-slate-200 sm:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="space-y-1">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-400">Frontend</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Astro + React + Tailwind</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-300">
            Mostly static pages with small interactive React islands, styled with Tailwind.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-1">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-400">Backend</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Serverless functions + Postgres</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-300">
            Lightweight APIs for comments and tools backed by a single relational database.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-1">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-400">Infra</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Vercel + managed Postgres</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-300">
            Zero-maintenance hosting with SSL, CI, and database integrations.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-400">Stack by layer</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-950/60 p-4 sm:p-5">
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Presentation & UI</h3>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="rounded-full border border-emerald-500/50 bg-emerald-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-emerald-200">
              Astro (site framework)
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-sky-500/50 bg-sky-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-sky-200">
              React (interactive islands)
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-indigo-500/50 bg-indigo-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-indigo-200">
              Tailwind CSS (design system)
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">
            Pages are mostly static for speed; React is only used where interactivity is needed (like the comments demo and future tools).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-2 border-t border-slate-800 pt-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">APIs & logic</h3>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="rounded-full border border-amber-500/50 bg-amber-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-amber-200">
              Vercel Serverless Functions
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-slate-500/50 bg-slate-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-200">
              Node.js runtime
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-fuchsia-500/50 bg-fuchsia-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-fuchsia-200">
              Nodemailer (transactional email)
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">
            Small, single-purpose functions are used for database-backed features and contact flows.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-2 border-t border-slate-800 pt-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Data & storage</h3>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="rounded-full border border-cyan-500/50 bg-cyan-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-cyan-200">
              PostgreSQL
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-teal-500/50 bg-teal-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-teal-200">
              Pooled client (`pg`)
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-rose-500/50 bg-rose-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-rose-200">
              AWS RDS / Aurora compatible
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">
            A single relational database stores comments, tools, and future idea-related data.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-2 border-t border-slate-800 pt-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Hosting & ops</h3>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="rounded-full border border-slate-500/50 bg-slate-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-200">
              Vercel (hosting, SSL, CDN)
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-slate-500/50 bg-slate-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-200">
              Environment configs via `dotenv`
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full border border-slate-500/50 bg-slate-500/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-200">
              Git + CI deploys
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">
            The site is deployed from Git pushes; environment variables control local vs. cloud database connections.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-400">Why this stack</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-950/60 p-4 text-sm text-slate-200">
        <p>
          The goal is to keep Palchat easy to maintain: static-first pages, a single database, and well-supported tools.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-xs text-slate-300 sm:text-sm">
          <li class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="mt-1 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-400" />
            <span><span class="font-medium text-slate-100">Fast by default</span> — most content is static, so pages are quick to load globally.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="mt-1 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-400" />
            <span><span class="font-medium text-slate-100">Small moving parts</span> — only a handful of serverless functions and one database.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="mt-1 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-indigo-400" />
            <span><span class="font-medium text-slate-100">Room to grow</span> — new tools can be added as self-contained pages using the same stack.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>
</Layout>

